## Technical Implementation

### HTML Structure
- Modern HTML5 semantic elements
- Clean, well-organized structure
- Mobile meta tags for responsive design

### CSS Implementation
- CSS in separate stylesheets (styles.css, fresh-styles.css)
- Custom properties (CSS variables) for colors and common values
- Media queries for responsive design

### JavaScript Functionality
- Network visualization using Canvas API
- Form validation
- Social authentication placeholders
- Phone number formatting
- Cookie consent management
- Mobile navigation handling

### Current Limitations
- Simple static pages without authentication
- No database integration
- Limited interactivity
- Form submission via FormSubmit.co service
- Mobile navigation has some positioning issues
- Network visualization not optimized for all devices

## Mobile Responsiveness

### Current Implementation
- Responsive design with breakpoints at 600px, 768px, and 900px
- Mobile-specific CSS adjustments
- Hamburger menu for mobile navigation

### Issues Identified
1. Mobile menu button positioning inconsistent across devices
2. Form elements sometimes overflow container on very small screens
3. Network visualization performance issues on lower-end devices
4. Country code selector UI challenges on narrow screens
5. Multiple media query declarations causing some specificity issues

## Performance Considerations

### Assets
- Limited use of images (mostly vector/SVG)
- No large media files
- CSS and JS files have some redundancy that could be optimized

### Loading
- No lazy loading implemented
- No critical CSS separation
- Script loading not optimized (no defer/async)

### Potential Optimizations
- Combine and minify CSS files
- Optimize JavaScript
- Implement proper asset loading strategies
- Add caching headers
- Optimize network visualization for performance

